      "commit_title": "[CUB] Delegate large segments to Multi-CTA Implementation in `DeviceSegmentedTopK` (#8522)",
      "commit_message": "* Adapt TopK agent\n\n* Update agent implementation\n\nSwitch from writing out all large segment parameters/pointers to just\nwriting out their IDs and the number of tiles needed from the large\nsegment kernel. This reduces the amount of memory and BW needed but\nadds a level of indirection to that kernel.\n\n* Dispatch modified small-segment kernel/agent\n\n* Finalize large segment handling\n\n- Use DeviceScan when there are no small segments\n- Put atomic counters into struct with cache line alignment for each\n  counter\n- Refactor tuning policy/-selector\n\n* Add missing include\n\n* Implement Feedback\n\n* Update copyright headers\n\n* Rework tuning policy\n\n- Add multi_worker_policy.\n- Pass it through the policy getter.\n\n* Fix guarantees that can not be per-segment.\n\n* Make sure types are propagated\n\n- Atomic large segment counter now uses offset type corresponding to\n  NumSegmentsParameterT::value_type\n- Large segment tile offsets (scan input/output) use\n  TotalNumItemsGuaranteeT::value_type\n\n* Re-add indirect num_segments type\n\nGive it a descriptive name (indirect instead of per_segment).\n\n* Implement feedback"
    },
